I"Ï<h2 id="definition">Definition</h2>

<p>TheÂ <code class="highlighter-rouge">@media</code>Â rule is used in media queries to apply different styles for different media types/devices.</p>

<p>Media queries can be used to check many things, such as:</p>

<ul>
  <li>width and height of the viewport</li>
  <li>width and height of the device</li>
  <li>orientation (is the tablet/phone in landscape or portrait mode?)</li>
  <li>resolution</li>
</ul>

<p>Media queries are used for the following:</p>

<ul>
  <li>To conditionally apply styles with theÂ <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS">CSS</a>Â <code class="highlighter-rouge">[@media]</code>(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@media)Â andÂ <code class="highlighter-rouge">[@import]</code>(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@import)Â <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/At-rule">at-rules.</a></li>
  <li>To target specific media for theÂ <code class="highlighter-rouge">[&lt;style&gt;]</code>(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/style),Â <code class="highlighter-rouge">[&lt;link&gt;]</code>(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/link),Â <code class="highlighter-rouge">[&lt;source&gt;]</code>(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/source), and otherÂ <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML">HTML</a>Â elements with theÂ <code class="highlighter-rouge">media=</code>Â attribute.</li>
  <li>ToÂ <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Media_Queries/Testing_media_queries">test and monitor media states</a>Â using theÂ <code class="highlighter-rouge">[Window.matchMedia()]</code>(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Window/matchMedia)Â andÂ <code class="highlighter-rouge">[MediaQueryList.addListener()]</code>(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/MediaQueryList/addListener)Â <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript">JavaScript</a>Â methods.</li>
</ul>

