<div class="language-css highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">@media</span> <span class="n">not</span><span class="err">|</span><span class="n">only</span> <span class="n">mediatype</span> <span class="n">and</span><span class="err">|</span><span class="n">not</span><span class="err">|</span><span class="n">only</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">media</span> <span class="n">feature</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
  <span class="nc">.my-code</span> <span class="p">{</span> <span class="err">â€¦</span> <span class="p">}</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<h3 id="media-types">Media Types</h3>

<p><em>Media types</em>Â describe the general category of a device. Except when using theÂ <code class="highlighter-rouge">not</code>Â orÂ <code class="highlighter-rouge">only</code>Â logical operators, the media type is optional and theÂ <code class="highlighter-rouge">all</code>Â type will be implied.</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong><code class="highlighter-rouge">all</code></strong>Suitable for all devices.</li>
  <li><strong><code class="highlighter-rouge">print</code></strong>Intended for paged material and documents viewed on a screen in print preview mode. (Please seeÂ <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Paged_Media">paged media</a>Â for information about formatting issues that are specific to these formats.)</li>
  <li><strong><code class="highlighter-rouge">screen</code></strong>Intended primarily for screens.</li>
  <li><strong><code class="highlighter-rouge">speech</code></strong>Intended for speech synthesizers.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="media-features">Media Features</h3>

<p><strong>Mostly used features</strong></p>

<ul>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">width</code></li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">min-width</code> / <code class="highlighter-rouge">max-width</code></li>
  <li><code class="highlighter-rouge">orientation</code> : portrait, landscape</li>
</ul>

<p><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/Media_Queries/Using_media_queries">Here</a> you have more information about the specifications.</p>

